        Find how to show with a ven diagram in python
    </p>
    <p>
        Let's use another example relation. If the two sets are equal we say that a relation from <m>A</m> to <m>A</m> is called a relation <term>on</term> <m>A</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
        <em>Example:</em> Let <m>A = \{2,3,4,6,8}</m> and <m>R</m> be the relation on <m>A</m> defined by <m>aRb</m> if <m>a</m> divides <m>b</m>. This is expressed as <m>a | b</m>
        <me>
            R = \{(2,2),(2,4),(2,6),(2,8),(3, 3),(3, 6),(4,4),(4,8),(6,6),(8, 8)\}
        </me>
    </p>
    <p>
        To make sense of the pairs in this relation we can ask does <m>2</m> divide <m>2</m>? Yes. <m>2</m> does not divide <m>3</m> so it is not included. Next, we see that <m>2</m> divides <m>4</m>, and we continue with this pattern.
    </p>
    <p>
        We can use a digraph to represent a relation on a set. A relation "on" is the relation of a set on itself. Create a node (vertex) for each element of the set. Use arrows pointing to nodes to represent the direction of the relation from one element to another. 
    </p>
    <p>
        Example: Let <m>A = \{1,2,3\}</m> and <m>R</m> be the relation of <m>A</m> defined by <m>aRb</m> if <m>a < b</m>.
    </p>
